# E2E Tests (Playwright)

E2E tests live in `apps/e2e/` and run against the full Docker Compose stack (admin + blog + Redis + nginx + PostgreSQL + MailHog).

## Running

```bash
npm run test:e2e                          # full suite (excludes @a11y in CI split)
npm run test:e2e -- --grep @a11y          # accessibility-only
```

## Conventions

- Place specs under `apps/e2e/tests/`. Shared fixtures go in `apps/e2e/fixtures/`.
- Tag accessibility specs with `@a11y` in the test title — the CI splits the run on this tag.
- A11y assertions use `axe-core` (via `@axe-core/playwright`); zero AA violations are required.
- Capture emails via MailHog (`http://localhost:8025`) — never hit a real SMTP server.
- Use stable selectors: `getByRole`, `getByLabel`, `getByTestId`. Avoid raw CSS class selectors that may change.
- Tests must be idempotent: clean up created entities or use unique data per run (timestamps, UUIDs).

## When to add an E2E test

Add an E2E spec for any **critical user flow**: login, post publish, comment moderation, newsletter double opt-in, RBAC denial, etc. Smaller behaviors stay as Vitest integration tests.
